WEBVTT

00:07.048 --> 00:08.966
Domain Expansion.

00:08.967 --> 00:10.719
Chimera Shadow Garden.

00:17.350 --> 00:19.811
Esoteric Technique. Hollow Wicker Basket.

00:22.397 --> 00:23.732
<i>Hollow Wicker Basket.</i>

00:24.524 --> 00:27.985
<i>The prototype
of New Shadow Style's Simple Domain.</i>

00:27.986 --> 00:29.987
<i>It neutralizes a domain</i>

00:29.988 --> 00:33.657
<i>and cancels out its sure-hit effect.</i>

00:33.658 --> 00:36.118
Too bad for you…

00:36.119 --> 00:39.747
<i>What Jogo and Hanami used in Shibuya,
Domain Amplification,</i>

00:39.748 --> 00:43.960
<i>creates a domain large enough
to carry a sure-hit, sure-kill effect…</i>

00:46.880 --> 00:48.881
<i>Why is it still hitting me?</i>

00:48.882 --> 00:51.884
<i>By deliberately not imbuing the domain
with a technique,</i>

00:51.885 --> 00:53.510
<i>it leaves space,</i>

00:53.511 --> 00:55.846
<i>allowing Gojo's technique to flow into it,</i>

00:55.847 --> 00:58.182
<i>thereby neutralizing the Limitless.</i>

00:58.183 --> 01:01.268
<i>Hollow Wicker Basket and Simple Domain</i>

01:01.269 --> 01:04.439
<i>cannot neutralize the technique itself.</i>

01:05.023 --> 01:08.901
<i>They neutralize the barrier
imbued with a technique,</i>

01:08.902 --> 01:13.364
<i>thereby nullifying the sure-hit effect
of the imbued technique.</i>

01:16.117 --> 01:19.411
<i>Fushiguro's domain is incomplete.</i>

01:19.412 --> 01:21.538
Your smirk is gone now.

01:21.539 --> 01:23.416
You little brat.

01:25.168 --> 01:26.960
<i>By repurposing the gym itself</i>

01:26.961 --> 01:30.464
<i>as his domain space,</i>

01:30.465 --> 01:32.217
<i>the forcibly closed barrier</i>

01:32.801 --> 01:35.637
<i>wasn't imbued with a sure-hit technique.</i>

01:37.263 --> 01:39.140
Why are you acting like you've won--

01:40.558 --> 01:42.351
<i>I see.</i>

01:42.352 --> 01:43.977
<i>Here, he used Chimera Shadow Garden</i>

01:43.978 --> 01:48.190
<i>to expand the Ten Shadows Technique</i>

01:48.191 --> 01:53.238
<i>and draw out 120% of its potential.</i>

01:53.738 --> 01:58.575
<i>But that half-baked state
caught Reggie Star off guard.</i>

01:58.576 --> 02:02.704
<i>This clone and those</i> shikigami
<i>had physical form before it touched me.</i>

02:02.705 --> 02:07.085
<i>Meaning this barrier isn't imbued
with a sure-hit technique.</i>

02:07.669 --> 02:11.713
<i>The technique boost
inside this domain is insane.</i>

02:11.714 --> 02:14.634
<i>It's way harder to deal with
than a normal sure-hit domain.</i>

02:15.135 --> 02:18.929
<i>If he brings out Max Elephant here
and presses me with a water attack,</i>

02:18.930 --> 02:21.808
<i>my options get cut in half,
and I'm basically done for!</i>

02:29.691 --> 02:33.235
<i>But of course,</i>

02:33.236 --> 02:35.947
<i>that isn't how it goes for me, right?</i>

02:37.198 --> 02:38.158
Nue!

02:42.829 --> 02:44.414
Too slow!

02:48.293 --> 02:49.836
I knew it.

02:52.005 --> 02:54.506
My footing has been weird for a while now.

02:54.507 --> 02:58.261
If it's not reinforced with cursed energy,
I feel like I am going to get sucked in.

03:01.973 --> 03:06.310
Everything underneath this domain
is all your shadow, right?

03:06.311 --> 03:09.771
You can store and pull out objects,
and even move yourself in and out.

03:09.772 --> 03:11.690
Handy, isn't it?

03:11.691 --> 03:13.860
But one thing had been bothering me.

03:14.360 --> 03:16.737
Your stockpile of weapons is pretty small.

03:16.738 --> 03:20.157
I've only seen
one cheap cursed tool so far.

03:20.158 --> 03:21.700
Either your capacity is tiny,

03:21.701 --> 03:26.288
and you always need to keep
enough room for yourself,

03:26.289 --> 03:27.123
or you're the one

03:27.790 --> 03:33.504
who has to bear the weight
of whatever is stored there.

03:34.714 --> 03:36.424
And bingo, it was the latter.

03:37.050 --> 03:40.510
I turned your domain's own setup
against you.

03:40.511 --> 03:42.679
Three passenger cars' worth.

03:42.680 --> 03:45.350
Right now, you weigh about 2.4 tons.

03:45.934 --> 03:48.185
Your clone couldn't take it,

03:48.186 --> 03:50.772
but can you still bring out
your <i>shikigami,</i> I wonder?

03:52.315 --> 03:55.484
Either way, I'll just watch my footing
and keep piling on the weight

03:55.485 --> 03:57.778
until you crush yourself

03:57.779 --> 04:00.114
under your own load.

04:02.659 --> 04:04.785
Aren't you forgetting something?

04:04.786 --> 04:06.203
What?

04:06.204 --> 04:09.749
Even unfinished, a domain is a domain.

04:11.876 --> 04:13.878
Above us is a shadow too!

04:25.765 --> 04:28.225
Let's see who breaks first!

04:28.226 --> 04:30.353
Reggie!

06:05.073 --> 06:07.991
<i>It's said that a human being
loses consciousness</i>

06:07.992 --> 06:10.495
<i>at around five to six Gs.</i>

06:11.079 --> 06:12.705
<i>2.4 tons…</i>

06:13.247 --> 06:16.416
<i>Assuming Fushiguro weighs 60 kilograms,</i>

06:16.417 --> 06:20.421
<i>his body was now under a 40 G load.</i>

06:21.547 --> 06:25.175
<i>To prevent G-forces from making blood pool
in his lower body</i>

06:25.176 --> 06:28.220
<i>and starving his brain of blood,</i>

06:28.221 --> 06:30.722
<i>Fushiguro lowered his stance</i>

06:30.723 --> 06:32.849
<i>and reinforced
his whole body with cursed energy,</i>

06:32.850 --> 06:35.728
<i>focusing especially on his lower half.</i>

06:37.313 --> 06:41.609
<i>An adult African elephant
weighs three to six tons.</i>

06:43.194 --> 06:46.404
<i>Due to the increased precision
inside the domain,</i>

06:46.405 --> 06:49.534
<i>Max Elephant was reproducing
that weight realistically.</i>

06:50.118 --> 06:53.787
<i>As for Reggie Star, who took it head-on,</i>

06:53.788 --> 06:55.998
<i>his right fibula
and calcaneus were cracked.</i>

06:57.250 --> 06:59.835
<i>Both of them were in a situation
where, one second later,</i>

06:59.836 --> 07:03.589
<i>it wouldn't have been strange
if they had both been crushed to death.</i>

07:05.091 --> 07:07.050
<i>I screwed up.</i>

07:07.051 --> 07:09.761
<i>If I had saved the truck,
this fight would've been over.</i>

07:09.762 --> 07:12.055
<i>What do I do?</i>

07:12.056 --> 07:16.059
<i>He splashed me with some water,
but my trump card is still safe!!</i>

07:16.060 --> 07:20.147
<i>I'll dive into the shadows,
then recreate my trump card from inside</i>

07:20.148 --> 07:22.442
<i>and crush him for good.</i>

07:24.610 --> 07:25.527
<i>No!</i>

07:25.528 --> 07:27.863
<i>The fact that he isn't releasing
the domain means</i>

07:27.864 --> 07:30.740
<i>that anything already swallowed up</i>

07:30.741 --> 07:33.327
<i>stays trapped inside
even after the domain ends!</i>

07:34.036 --> 07:35.829
<i>And if I get stuck in there forever</i>

07:35.830 --> 07:37.874
<i>after he dies…</i>

07:38.749 --> 07:41.209
<i>What even is it like in there?</i>

07:41.210 --> 07:44.755
<i>It's like liquid, but can you breathe?</i>

07:45.631 --> 07:49.593
<i>No, diving into the shadows
is way too risky.</i>

07:49.594 --> 07:52.388
<i>I'll do it right here, in this state!</i>

07:53.431 --> 07:56.976
<i>I'll bring out my trump card
and activate it!</i>

08:00.730 --> 08:03.648
Contractual Re-Creation!

08:03.649 --> 08:06.194
PLOP

08:23.544 --> 08:25.212
<i>Too late.</i>

08:25.213 --> 08:28.341
<i>And just as I thought,
there's no oxygen inside the shadows!</i>

08:29.967 --> 08:32.595
<i>No buoyancy. No drag.</i>

08:35.389 --> 08:36.474
<i>You just…</i>

08:38.392 --> 08:40.061
<i>sink…</i>

08:41.062 --> 08:41.896
<i>My consciousness…</i>

08:43.523 --> 08:44.732
<i>is…</i>

08:50.655 --> 08:52.989
<i>Not yet. Hang in there.</i>

08:52.990 --> 08:55.867
<i>I'll release the domain
only after he definitely dies!</i>

08:55.868 --> 08:58.663
<i>Then I can eject
everything inside the shadows!</i>

09:31.404 --> 09:33.738
The things I recreate disappear

09:33.739 --> 09:37.951
as soon as they carry out
the order I give them.

09:37.952 --> 09:41.288
I didn't give the submerged cars
any order.

09:41.289 --> 09:43.958
Couldn't have them disappearing,
after all.

09:44.458 --> 09:47.711
Which means there was still room
to give one a command.

09:47.712 --> 09:50.422
Bring me up with you.

09:50.423 --> 09:54.844
One car's worth of weight vanished,
but thanks to that, I made it out alive.

09:59.015 --> 10:00.515
I'll give it to you.

10:00.516 --> 10:02.643
You're strong.

10:03.144 --> 10:04.395
But I'm…

10:06.063 --> 10:07.898
stronger.

10:08.399 --> 10:11.736
Contractual Re-Creation!

10:16.907 --> 10:19.492
A two-story wooden house

10:19.493 --> 10:22.412
with a footprint of 40 <i>tsubo</i>!

10:22.413 --> 10:25.790
Just the frame alone
has to weigh at least 30 tons!

10:25.791 --> 10:28.419
Get crushed already!

11:01.661 --> 11:03.286
<i>What happened?</i>

11:03.287 --> 11:05.748
<i>Did I fall into the shadows again?</i>

11:07.124 --> 11:11.087
<i>No. This is real water. Why?</i>

11:11.962 --> 11:16.132
<i>I feel heavy. Is that brat
the one holding me down?</i>

11:16.133 --> 11:18.468
<i>What ridiculous strength…</i>

11:18.469 --> 11:20.220
<i>No, wait…</i>

11:20.221 --> 11:23.766
<i>Is it because of the extra weight
from the two cars I added?</i>

11:25.851 --> 11:26.977
<i>This is bad…</i>

11:27.478 --> 11:29.230
<i>This time, I really will sink.</i>

11:29.939 --> 11:32.900
<i>I need to cancel Contractual Re-Creation.</i>

11:51.168 --> 11:53.002
<i>I get it…</i>

11:53.003 --> 11:54.921
<i>This is the gymnasium.</i>

11:54.922 --> 11:58.092
<i>And below it, in the lower basement,
there's a heated swimming pool!</i>

12:01.053 --> 12:03.596
<i>So he escaped into the shadows,
then released the domain,</i>

12:03.597 --> 12:07.351
<i>then had me break the floor
and drop us into the pool?</i>

12:10.896 --> 12:14.024
Now that you're that soaked,
those receipts are useless.

12:18.529 --> 12:21.656
<i>You didn't follow up right away.
You waited.</i>

12:21.657 --> 12:24.952
<i>You restored your technique
after exhausting it in the domain.</i>

12:26.036 --> 12:29.123
So then, what about you?

12:29.957 --> 12:33.419
You can't summon
any <i>shikigami</i> now, can you?

12:34.837 --> 12:37.922
Yes. You know it too.

12:37.923 --> 12:39.258
From here on out…

12:40.676 --> 12:44.387
<i>Whatever you summon,
it's not going to be the dog.</i>

12:44.388 --> 12:46.681
<i>And none of the others
has the finishing power.</i>

12:46.682 --> 12:48.475
<i>Go ahead and use one.</i>

12:48.476 --> 12:52.104
<i>The moment you do, I'll catch you slipping
and kill you with a counter!</i>

13:42.863 --> 13:45.824
Divine Dog is not so weak
that it would be out of action

13:46.325 --> 13:47.326
from just that.

13:48.577 --> 13:52.498
Sorcerers live and die by lying…

14:09.306 --> 14:12.351
That domain and the drowning plan.

14:13.060 --> 14:17.605
And hiding the dog card
while making me think you had lost it.

14:17.606 --> 14:21.234
So, you didn't run into the gymnasium.

14:21.235 --> 14:22.945
You lured me there.

14:23.571 --> 14:25.446
Didn't expect to get outplayed

14:25.447 --> 14:29.285
by a modern sorcerer,
and a brat like you at that.

14:31.203 --> 14:34.582
Even if I wanted to run,
Nue can't carry a person for long.

14:35.082 --> 14:37.042
I learned that the hard way before.

14:43.090 --> 14:46.844
You… What's your connection to Tengen?

14:50.639 --> 14:52.474
Tengen?

14:54.643 --> 14:58.397
Oh, right. So she's still alive, huh?

14:59.315 --> 15:01.608
That shut-in?

15:01.609 --> 15:03.277
I see. That's enough.

15:05.446 --> 15:09.283
<i>Reggie called Tengen's explanation
of the Culling Game's purpose a bluff.</i>

15:10.367 --> 15:13.286
<i>I should consider the chance
that Tengen and Kenjaku</i>

15:13.287 --> 15:17.416
<i>are working together,
and fed us a fake objective…</i>

15:18.208 --> 15:20.294
<i>But from his reaction, probably not…</i>

15:24.632 --> 15:25.925
Kogane.

15:26.467 --> 15:30.012
Give this guy all my points.

15:33.265 --> 15:37.518
Forty-one points have been transferred
from Reggie Star.

15:37.519 --> 15:38.771
What are you playing at?

15:39.647 --> 15:42.690
That's a hell of a way to ask.

15:42.691 --> 15:45.444
I'm doing one good deed at the very end.

15:46.278 --> 15:48.780
I'm just a bystander.

15:48.781 --> 15:51.408
It's not like Kenjaku and I
are best friends.

15:52.076 --> 15:55.621
I've just got a feeling
this will make things more interesting…

15:56.121 --> 15:58.123
Just a hunch.

15:59.541 --> 16:03.545
Do me a favor.
You were the one who killed me.

16:04.546 --> 16:07.840
So let fate toy with you,

16:07.841 --> 16:11.470
and let you die a clown.

16:34.410 --> 16:36.912
Five points have been added.

16:49.883 --> 16:51.301
Did you get him?

16:51.969 --> 16:53.971
No, don't let your guard down.

16:55.723 --> 16:58.350
- He's persistent.
- What the hell?

16:59.018 --> 17:01.102
Why are you covered in lotion?

17:01.103 --> 17:02.562
It could be thick sauce.

17:02.563 --> 17:04.023
Shut up and die!

17:05.691 --> 17:08.151
Wait, it really is thick sauce?

17:08.152 --> 17:11.320
<i>What the hell is with this guy?</i>

17:11.321 --> 17:13.489
<i>I've blasted him over and over.</i>

17:13.490 --> 17:15.492
<i>That should've killed him five times over!</i>

17:15.993 --> 17:18.327
<i>How has he only taken this much damage?</i>

17:18.328 --> 17:19.871
ONLY THIS MUCH

17:19.872 --> 17:20.956
You hate thick sauce?

17:21.790 --> 17:24.376
<i>And those first wounds
he had are gone too.</i>

17:24.960 --> 17:28.630
<i>But it doesn't feel like
he used reverse cursed technique like me.</i>

17:29.882 --> 17:31.550
<i>None of this makes any sense.</i>

17:32.259 --> 17:33.551
Hazenoki.

17:33.552 --> 17:35.011
What?

17:35.012 --> 17:38.223
Reggie Star has passed away.

17:42.352 --> 17:43.269
What's wrong?

17:43.270 --> 17:46.147
I'm leaving. Screw this.

17:46.148 --> 17:47.231
I see.

17:47.232 --> 17:49.401
Take a bath and brush your teeth.

17:52.571 --> 17:55.074
How about 100 points, Kanchi?

17:55.574 --> 17:56.866
Stop following me.

17:56.867 --> 18:00.453
Come on,
just like ordering soba on New Year's.

18:00.454 --> 18:01.288
Drop dead.

18:01.872 --> 18:04.415
<i>Takaba's technique, Comedian,</i>

18:04.416 --> 18:08.961
<i>makes anything he's certain
is funny become reality.</i>

18:08.962 --> 18:12.925
<i>It's a technique that could even rival
Satoru Gojo's.</i>

18:14.676 --> 18:17.595
<i>Takaba knows absolutely nothing</i>

18:17.596 --> 18:19.515
<i>about his own technique.</i>

18:27.981 --> 18:29.899
<i>I don't know!</i>

18:29.900 --> 18:33.195
<i>Once you grow up, there are many things
you just don't understand!</i>

18:39.118 --> 18:41.828
<i>I've heard men are wolves,</i>

18:41.829 --> 18:45.874
<i>but it's always the wolves
who sort out things I don't understand!</i>

18:49.920 --> 18:52.839
<i>The wolves always do everything,</i>

18:52.840 --> 18:55.758
<i>so I don't have to think
about anything at all.</i>

18:55.759 --> 18:58.762
<i>That's because I'm cute, right?</i>

19:05.602 --> 19:08.605
<i>Wolves always… always…</i>

19:17.322 --> 19:19.908
<i>That's not okay, Megumi.</i>

19:27.249 --> 19:28.083
Are you sure?

19:36.675 --> 19:38.218
Shut up.

19:41.680 --> 19:43.557
Damn sis…

20:03.285 --> 20:05.536
<i>Things moved quickly in the Sendai Colony.</i>

20:05.537 --> 20:06.329
MIYAGI PREFECTURE, SENDAI CITY
NOVEMBER 12TH, 11:28

20:06.330 --> 20:07.955
<i>The fight there far surpassed</i>

20:07.956 --> 20:11.627
<i>the Tokyo Colonies in terms of ferocity.</i>

20:13.879 --> 20:15.713
<i>Dhruv Lakdawalla.</i>

20:15.714 --> 20:18.466
<i>Currently holding 91 points.</i>

20:18.467 --> 20:20.010
<i>His second incarnation.</i>

20:21.053 --> 20:22.553
<i>An elder who single-handedly</i>

20:22.554 --> 20:26.225
<i>subjugated the archipelago
during the Wa Civil War.</i>

20:27.017 --> 20:29.435
<i>He uses two autonomous</i> shikigami

20:29.436 --> 20:33.523
<i>and treats their trajectories
as his domain.</i>

20:36.777 --> 20:38.486
<i>Ryu Ishigori.</i>

20:38.487 --> 20:41.323
<i>Currently holding 77 points.</i>

20:41.907 --> 20:46.078
<i>A cannon with the highest
cursed energy output among the players.</i>

20:47.996 --> 20:51.375
<i>Takako Uro. Currently holds 70 points.</i>

20:52.376 --> 20:55.253
<i>Former captain
of the Fujiwara assassination unit,</i>

20:55.254 --> 20:57.798
<i>the Sun, Moon, and Stars Squad.</i>

20:58.298 --> 21:01.593
<i>She has a technique
that manipulates the sky.</i>

21:02.970 --> 21:07.181
<i>Kurourushi. Currently holds 54 points.</i>

21:07.182 --> 21:11.102
<i>A cockroach curse Kenjaku released</i>

21:11.103 --> 21:13.104
<i>from Curse Manipulation control.</i>

21:13.105 --> 21:16.817
<i>Special Grade, registered.</i>

21:18.193 --> 21:21.780
<i>Dormant until its release conditions are met.</i>

21:23.407 --> 21:24.824
<i>No alliances.</i>

21:24.825 --> 21:28.661
<i>A four-way deadlock
built on equal strength</i>

21:28.662 --> 21:31.206
<i>and tangled compatibilities.</i>

21:31.748 --> 21:34.293
<i>But one corner of that balance…</i>

21:36.044 --> 21:37.170
<i>has fallen.</i>

21:38.839 --> 21:40.923
<i>Yuta Okkotsu.</i>

21:40.924 --> 21:43.468
<i>Currently holds 35 points.</i>

21:44.303 --> 21:49.015
<i>Three months after the Night Parade
of a Hundred Demons,</i>

21:49.016 --> 21:52.477
<i>he regained his place as a Special Grade.
Second only to Satoru Gojo.</i>

21:53.061 --> 21:54.062
<i>A true prodigy.</i>

23:27.614 --> 23:29.198
<i>I'll get the 400 points</i>

23:29.199 --> 23:31.826
<i>- on my own.</i>
- <i>Yuta, which one do you want?</i>

23:31.827 --> 23:33.828
- <i>Yeah, that's Kurourushi.</i>
- <i>All of it.</i>

23:33.829 --> 23:36.413
<i>Give Yuta back!</i>

23:36.414 --> 23:39.333
<i>I won't have Sensei
kill his best friend twice.</i>

23:39.334 --> 23:40.919
NEXT EPISODE
